== Methodology Synthesis

This chapter operationalizes the paper's core methodological claim: security quality for LLM applications is demonstrated through iterative evidence loops, not static one-time checks. The method links threat assumptions, attack execution, control deployment, and measurable outcomes in one coherent process.

Research gap note: many existing AI-security discussions either emphasize attack novelty or enumerate controls, but fewer provide a rigorous bridge between both. The methodology presented here addresses that gap by making traceability and comparability first-class design goals.

Threats-to-validity note: conclusions remain conditional on scenario coverage and platform stability. Subsequent chapters therefore treat findings as evidence-backed but context-bound, and they retain explicit residual-risk statements where uncertainty remains.
